<!--
  OWASP Dependency-Check suppression baseline for AgentForge4j.

  Empty on purpose. Dependency-Check runs in ADVISORY mode (scheduled CI only; not bound to the
  normal `verify` build) until this baseline and the NVD API key are stable, after which it is
  promoted to gating (failBuildOnCVSS). Add a <suppress> block here ONLY for a triaged,
  accepted finding, with a <notes> entry recording the CVE, the affected dependency, and the
  rationale (e.g. not reachable, false positive, fixed-by transitive override).

  Example shape (do not enable without justification):
    <suppress>
      <notes>CVE-XXXX-YYYYY: not reachable; the vulnerable codepath is never invoked.</notes>
      <gav regex="true">^com\.example:lib:.*$</gav>
      <cve>CVE-XXXX-YYYYY</cve>
    </suppress>
-->
